  <description type="morphology">Plants tiny, olive green.  Leaves linear-lanceolate to ovate-lanceolate, stoutly subulate from ovate base, narrowly obtuse; costae ending in apex, filling subula; margins serrulate; leaf cells (1–)2:1; perichaetial leaves somewhat larger, similar to vegetative leaves, not much differentiated.  Seta 1.3–1.6 mm, straight to slightly flexuose, slender.  Capsule hemispheric to turbinate, wider than long, widest at mouth only when old; peristome none, columella immersed.  Spores 11–14 µm.</description>
